SUMMARY:Early Childhood Mandarin Music and Movement Class
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a 30-minute Mandarin Music & Movement class specially designed for young learners. We will sing\, move\, play instruments\, and tell stories. We welcome all levels of Mandarin fluency from absolute beginners to native Mandarin speakers. Recommended for children six and under accompanied by their caregivers. No registration is required and on a first come basis.\n\nHeart Strings Mandarin is an Early Childhood Mandarin Music and Movement program designed for young children. Created by a bilingual language and music educator with professional qualifications in music therapy and mental health\, this program offers a warm\, engaging introduction to Mandarin through music.\n\nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/early-childhood-mandarin-music-and-movement-class-19/
LOCATION:Beaverton Library Murray Scholls
CATEGORIES:Educational,Family Fun,Kids Calendar,Music,Storytime
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_1760-rotated.jpeg
